body.name: CORSAIR VENGEANCE SODIMM DDR5 RAM 16GB (2x8GB) 4800MHz CL40 Intel XMP iCUE Compatible Computer Memory - Black (CMSX16GX5M2A4800C40)
features: Upgrade Your DDR5 Gaming or Performance Laptop: DDR5 SODIMM memory modules deliver faster frequencies, greater capacities, lower power consumption, and high performance to tackle the most demanding tasks, games, and workloads.

Compatible with Nearly Any Intel and AMD System: Industry-standard SODIMM form-factor is compatible with a wide range of popular Intel and AMD gaming and performance laptops, small-form-factor PCs, and Intel NUC kits.
Easy Installation: Simple installation process – just a screwdriver is required for most laptops.
Maximum Speed Boost: VENGEANCE SODIMM automatically sets to maximum speed on compatible systems for faster load times, multitasking, and more – no need to set in BIOS.
Rigorously Tested Reliability: Thoroughly screened and tested to ensure superior performance and reliability.
body.description: Upgrade your DDR5 gaming or performance laptop with cutting-edge CORSAIR VENGEANCE SERIES DDR5 SODIMM memory modules. Compatible with a wide range of Intel and AMD laptops and small-form-factor PCs, VENGEANCE SODIMM upgrades your existing memory, harnessing the faster frequencies and greater capacities of DDR5. Modules automatically set to maximum system speeds for faster load times and smoother multitasking, and installation is quick and easy – just a screwdriver is needed for most laptops. VENGEANCE SODIMM is compatible with Intel XMP 3.0 on high-frequency kits for exceptional performance. Each module is rigorously screened, thoroughly tested, and backed by a lifetime limited warranty to ensure high performance and reliability, granting your laptop an instant boost.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 11, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Like title says, amazing product. It was a plug and play upgrade for my laptop. At first, I was skeptical since I reached out to ASUS support to see if these would work. They could neither confirm nor deny that these specific ram would work. Additionally, the ASUS website states that the max RAM upgrade is 32GB. I ended up buying these and thankfully it works flawlessly. I am assuming that the 32GB are for 1 RAM. So total max RAM upgrade is 64GB (2x32). The laptop I installed these on are the ASUS ROG G713PV (2023) for anyone who’s wondering.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 17, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great for Asus Zephyrus G14!
reviews.reviewText: My Asus Zephyrus G14 (2023) came with only 16GB of RAM soldered to the board. I bought this to extend it to 48gb. Works perfectly! Took about 2 minutes to post after the first boot for the whole automatic memory timing thing that Zen4 does. Be patient and it will come up quickly. All boots after are lightning fast.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 3, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars So far so good m17 r5 AMD 6900hx, 3070ti
reviews.reviewText: I took a chance and so far, so good but it didn't look good for a moment.I'm not sure all Alienware m17 r5s are upgradable. Depending on the graphics card, you may have less options. I may be thinking about the extra SSD slot my model has.Anyways, I got the 64 gig kit from this listing and put it in after disconnecting the battery from motherboard.I was expecting a long boot time and possible failure.The laptop took two minutes before the power/ alien head flashed 3 times red then two times blue (or 3 blue 2 red, I'd make a terrible witness sorry)I thought oh well, this ram won't work...I got an Alienware splash screen that said F2 for bios setup or F12 for boot options. I tried hitting F2 and nothing happened so I held F2 and the power button for 20 seconds or so and surprisingly the laptop booted into Windows. I don't know if simply holding the power button would have done the same. I never entered the bios menu.I opened Lightroom and Photoshop and played quake champions for 30 minutes or so with those programs still open. Task manager was reporting around 50% of the ram was being used.So far, seems stable, will update if that changes.

reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars IS NOT COMPATIBLE WITH ALIENWARE LAPTOPS
reviews.reviewText: Although the features are as stated and the corsair website "guarantees" that they are compatible with alienware laptops, they are not. Do not buy this product if you have a laptop of that brand, and much less buy if you do not live in the US. AMAZON DOES NOT TAKE ANY RESPONSIBILITY FOR THE RETURN if the product was purchased for abroad, and therefore you lose the money because the cost of returning the product is almost the same as the product itself.Pese a que las caracteristicas son las señaladas y la pagina web de corsair "garantiza" que son compatibles con portatiles alienware, no lo son. No comprar este producto si tienes un portatil de esa marca, y mucho menos compres si no vives en EEUU. AMAZON NO SE HACE CARGO DE LA DEVOLUCIÓN especialmente si el producto fue comprado por alguien fuera del territorio continental de los EEUU. El costo de devolución es casi el mismo del producto, y por tanto es dinero perdido.
En general me gusto para la actualización de mi Asus Rog G16. La instalación muy sencilla, todo bien.
